com.conichi.sdk.core.dataprovider

Class CNICloudProvider<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.conichi.sdk.core.dataprovider.CNILocalProvider<T>
      • com.conichi.sdk.core.dataprovider.CNICloudProvider<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Clearable, CNIEntityFromSourceProvider<T>, CNIEntityProvider<T>, CNIObservable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CNIDefaultNotificationsProvider, CNIDefaultPublicVenuesProvider, CNIDefaultStatusProvider, CNIDefaultUserProvider

    public abstract class CNICloudProvider<T>
extends CNILocalProvider<T>
implements CNIEntityFromSourceProvider<T>, CNIObservable<T>
    CNIEntityFromSourceProvider implementation which provides caching mechanism that saves data in both persistent storage and memory(RAM).
    Main difference between this and CNILocalProvider is that CNICloudProvider will automatically load the data from server if cache is empty.

    In case if you need to obtain the data from specific source (server or local cache) - use getEntity(DataSource):

  • DataSource.CLOUD - to fetch the latest data from server and cache it
  • DataSource.LOCAL - to obtain cached data

    • The common case is that your app received push notification and you know that data for specific data provider has been changed - in this case you have to call getEntity(DataSource) with DataSource.CLOUD argument
